Release 2.0
2026-07-01

Modernization for current PostgreSQL and PHP.  Tested on PostgreSQL 13 through
18 with PHP 8.3 (embed SAPI, non-thread-safe).

* Ported the C code to PostgreSQL 18 APIs: FunctionCallInfo args[] (PG12),
  TupleDescAttr (PG10), SearchSysCache1, strlcpy, TextDatumGetCString,
  ALLOCSET_DEFAULT_SIZES, uint64 SPI row counts (PG11), and the removal of
  SPI_restore_connection (PG10).
* Ported the interpreter glue to the PHP 8 Zend API: new zval/refcount model,
  hash-table and resource APIs, calling convention (call_user_function),
  symbol-table access (zend_rebuild_symbol_table), embed startup, and the
  PHP 8.1+ zend_error_cb signature.
* Uncaught PHP exceptions (e.g. calling an undefined function or a type error)
  are now reported as PostgreSQL errors instead of silently returning NULL.
* PHP deprecations (such as the "${var}" string-interpolation syntax) are now
  non-fatal notices rather than errors.
* Replaced the obsolete pg_pltemplate install scripts with a real extension:
  "CREATE EXTENSION plphp".
* Replaced the autoconf build with a PGXS Makefile.
* Added features for parity with PL/Perl: anonymous DO code blocks (an inline
  handler), prepared statements (spi_prepare / spi_exec_prepared /
  spi_query_prepared / spi_freeplan), SQL quoting helpers (quote_literal /
  quote_nullable / quote_ident), a full elog(level, message) supporting
  DEBUG/LOG/INFO/NOTICE/WARNING/ERROR, and transaction control (spi_commit /
  spi_rollback) in procedures called via CALL in a non-atomic context.
  See doc/plperl-comparison.md.
* Added features for parity with PL/Tcl: event trigger functions (RETURNS
  event_trigger, with $_TD['event']/$_TD['tag']), explicit subtransactions
  (subtransaction(callable, ...)), module autoloading from a plphp_modules
  table, and a plphp.start_proc GUC run at interpreter init.
  See doc/pltcl-comparison.md.
* Verified on PostgreSQL 13 through 18.  Version guards keep older releases
  working: MarkGUCPrefixReserved on PG 15+ (EmitWarningsOnPlaceholders before),
  and an explicit SPI_start_transaction after spi_commit/spi_rollback before
  PG 15.  A base_1.out variant covers the pre-PG 17 array-dimension error text.
* Regression suite refreshed; all 17 tests pass on PostgreSQL 13-18 / PHP 8.3.
  The currently-disabled out/varnames tests were re-enabled and compat/txn/
  evttrig/subxact/modules tests for the new features were added.

Note: PHP's "safe_mode" was removed in PHP 5.4, so PL/php can no longer be
sandboxed.  It is now an UNTRUSTED, superuser-only language (created without the
TRUSTED attribute); the previous "plphpu" variant was dropped as redundant.
See the SECURITY NOTE in README.

